race.comment: LET'S FLY (4) has two duck eggs next to her name but they have been in the $500k Four Pillars and Group 3 Angst. Very fit mare facing a massive class drop today. Steps up to 1800m, a trip she won over at her only try. Expecting big things. AGITA (5) failed in the Four Pillars most recently. Won a BM72 over this course and distance three back by 2.2 lengths. Capable of turning things around in this far more suitable contest. BUCKENARA (9) has won two on the trot at the provincials, the latest over a mile at Kembla. Untried at this distance but is by Dundeel so expect he will run it out. DUE CALZINI (7) is racing extra well in open company out of town. Must be included. SOSINO (1) ran a better race last start and out to 1800m at the fourth run back from a spell looks a nice scenario.
